node.text:
Directed and shot by @alivelikethewind, @beyondthebeat, @windcollective (@alivelikethewind) “This video is a celebration of black culture. You see, the beauty, the power, the energy that we possess is just as important a narrative right now. I’m committed to sharing more of our heart and blessing this world with our perspective.
.
I dreamed up this video with the @windcollective team and we had to make it. We shot it across several Wind Collective Travel Experiences Im 2019. I remember feeling blessed to capture and share the energy of my people.
.
Black people - It may be our time to mourn but it is also our time to be joyful because change is coming. It may be our time to march in the streets and it also our time to stand bold, proud of who we are. My black kings and queens - there is a renaissance occurring. Stay woke and stay vibesy. Love you all.”
.
Here’s a reminder from the script of the video - “Being Black. It’s not mediocre. Nor is it a limit. Its your greatest asset. Your secret weapon. It’s history, and struggle and rising. It’s beauty and birthright and excellence. We are the culture - In Black.”

node.title: Being Black - We are the Culture

node.text:
Prints for Wildlife is Back! 🦁 

There are so many mental barriers & real barriers between dreaming up something and actually making it happen. 

When our friends @pie_aerts & @ladyvenom and founded @printsforwildlife 15 months ago, they both didn’t really know if and how it would take off…

@pie_aerts :

“But 1 thing we did know, we wanted to help. Over the past few years the African continent has given me so much and therefore building @printsforwildlife became my way of doing something back. My way of thanking the African people for their kind spirits, their beautiful energy and their warm hospitality. My way of thanking all those rangers that fight day and night for the protection of our last wild places.

After months of work, today is a special day. We are launching our second campaign and seeing the first 125 images hit the world is a scary and exciting feeling at the same time. I honestly could not be more proud of the community we created. More than 170 photographers and thousands of people around the world purchasing prints.

Over the next 4 weeks we will keep surprising you with new images and together we will push to raise 1 million dollar for conservation. Because whereas some countries are already re-opening and have high vaccination rates, for many African countries the challenges still remain. The tourism sector is still at an all-time low, along with critical revenue for wildlife and communities. And there’s one thing we should all remember. In order to save nature, we should protect people first. And that’s exactly what our partner @africanparksnetwork is doing. Creating environments where people feel safe so that there’s room for them to appreciate the beauty of the world around them. Therefore on behalf of @africanparksnetwork and our @printsforwildlife team, I am forever grateful for your support. 

Together we have built a little beacon of hope in these uncertain times, a light in the end of the tunnel.
Thank you to all you for making this happen!”
